             </p>
             <p>
                In its most basic sense, a podcast is a program made in a digital format for download over the internet. Typically, a user will download a podcast directly to their own personal device for listening later. Invented back in 2000, podcasts have exploded in popularity, occupying different areas such as sports, politics, or even fictional podcasts. Now, most podcasting is done by streaming using such apps as Spotify or Apple Podcasts, which is essentially downloading the podcast simultaneously as you listen to it, instead of prior. 
